node.text:
What a joy it was celebrating this beautiful girls birthday the other day!! Such a fun time & great reminder that despite all the horrible news we’re constantly getting thrown at us in the world right now, God is still on the throne and in control!!! He’s still working all things together for our good, He’s still our provider, He’s still opening opportunities, He’s still healing, and He’s still performing miracles!! My girl Kate right here is proof of that :)) Choosing to search for and focus on the miracles still happening all around us because even though the world right now might not be good, God still is!!! 💛

Way Maker.
Miracle Worker.
Promise Keeper.
Light in the Darkness.
My God, That is Who You Are!!!

node.text:
celebration > comparison !!! 🦋✨
Can we talk for a sec?? ;)

Have y’all ever found yourselves in situations where you genuinely want to be happy for someone else but for some reason feelings of jealously overtake you?? Well I’ve totally been there!! And let me tell you, not only is it the worst, but it’s also a trap.

There is a unique plan, a calling, an individual purpose for YOUR life that was placed over you when God created you. There is something inside of you that this world needs, something that nobody else has but YOU. Every little detail about you, the way you look, your personality, the things you love, were all intentionally placed inside of you to help fulfill this purpose. Crazy right?? 🤯

Can you guess what the first thing is that stops us from walking in our individual callings and ultimately living a fulfilling life? Focusing and trying to walk in someone else’s!! Only when we walk in our own callings will we feel truly fulfilled.

When we realize that not only are we each individually chosen by God & that He has a plan for each of our lives, but that someone else’s success doesn’t hinder ours, we become unstoppable!! Because only then can comparison end, and celebration begin!!! Our gifts compliment one another and make us powerful!! We need each other 🤍

Tag someone you’re proud of to celebrate them ✨
